ght end, season: 17 (2011)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/pgl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=single&year_min=1950&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=TE&game_type=R&career_game_num_min=1&career_game_num_max=400&game_num_min=0&game_num_max=99&week_num_min=0&week_num_max=99&c1stat=rec_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=10&c5val=1.0&order_by=rec_td|title=Most TD receptions by a TE, single season|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n* Most total touchdowns by a tight end, season: 18 (2011)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/psl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=single&year_min=1920&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=te&draft_year_min=1936&draft_year_max=2018&draft_slot_min=1&draft_slot_max=500&draft_pick_in_round=pick_overall&conference=any&draft_pos%5B%5D=qb&draft_pos%5B%5D=rb&draft_pos%5B%5D=wr&draft_pos%5B%5D=te&draft_pos%5B%5D=e&draft_pos%5B%5D=t&draft_pos%5B%5D=g&draft_pos%5B%5D=c&draft_pos%5B%5D=ol&draft_pos%5B%5D=dt&draft_pos%5B%5D=de&draft_pos%5B%5D=dl&draft_pos%5B%5D=ilb&draft_pos%5B%5D=olb&draft_pos%5B%5D=lb&draft_pos%5B%5D=cb&draft_pos%5B%5D=s&draft_pos%5B%5D=db&draft_pos%5B%5D=k&draft_pos%5B%5D=p&c1stat=all_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=10&c5val=1.0&order_by=all_td|title=Most TDs by a TE, single-season|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n* Youngest player with 3 touchdown receptions in a game: 21 years, 184 days (2010, vs. [[Pittsburgh Steelers]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/pgl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=game&year_min=1950&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=QB&pos%5B%5D=WR&pos%5B%5D=RB&pos%5B%5D=TE&pos%5B%5D=OL&pos%5B%5D=DL&pos%5B%5D=LB&pos%5B%5D=DB&game_type=R&career_game_num_min=1&career_game_num_max=400&game_num_min=0&game_num_max=99&week_num_min=0&week_num_max=99&c1stat=rec_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=3&c5val=1.0&order_by=age&order_by_asc=Y|title=Players with 3 TD in a game, by age|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Career records:''\n* Most offensive touchdowns in first two seasons: 28 (tied with [[Randy Moss]])\n* Most seasons with 10+ touchdowns by a tight end: 5 (2010\u201312, 2014\u201315)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/psl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=total&year_min=1920&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=te&draft_year_min=1936&draft_year_max=2018&draft_slot_min=1&draft_slot_max=500&draft_pick_in_round=pick_overall&conference=any&draft_pos%5B%5D=qb&draft_pos%5B%5D=rb&draft_pos%5B%5D=wr&draft_pos%5B%5D=te&draft_pos%5B%5D=e&draft_pos%5B%5D=t&draft_pos%5B%5D=g&draft_pos%5B%5D=c&draft_pos%5B%5D=ol&draft_pos%5B%5D=dt&draft_pos%5B%5D=de&draft_pos%5B%5D=dl&draft_pos%5B%5D=ilb&draft_pos%5B%5D=olb&draft_pos%5B%5D=lb&draft_pos%5B%5D=cb&draft_pos%5B%5D=s&draft_pos%5B%5D=db&draft_pos%5B%5D=k&draft_pos%5B%5D=p&c1stat=all_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=10&c5val=1.0&order_by=pass_td|title=Seasons with 10+ TD by a TE|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n* Most career average receiving yards per game among tight ends: 68.3<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/news/this-stat-shows-why-rob-gronkowski-is-retiring-at-the-perfect-time/ar-BBVaVGx?li=BBnbcA1|title=This stat shows why Rob Gronkowski is retiring at the perfect time|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref>\n* Most career touchdowns per game average among tight ends: 0.69<ref name=\":5\" />\n* Most yards per target average among tight ends: 9.9 (since 1992)<ref name=\":5\" />\n* First tight end to have 3 seasons with 10+ touchdowns and 1,000+ receiving yards (2011, 2014\u201315)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/eye-on-football/25412985/patriots-whip-the-texans-in-gronks-triumphant-return-10-things-to-know|title=Patriots whip the Texans in Gronk's triumphant return: 10 things to know|last1=Wilson|first1=Ryan|work=CBSSports.com|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref>\n* Consecutive seasons with 10+ touchdowns by a tight end: 3 (2010\u201312)\n* Most seasons of 1,000+ yards receiving by a tight end: 4 (tied with [[Tony Gonzalez]] and [[Jason Witten]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/psl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=total&year_min=1920&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=te&draft_year_min=1936&draft_year_max=2018&draft_slot_min=1&draft_slot_max=500&draft_pick_in_round=pick_overall&conference=any&draft_pos%5B%5D=qb&draft_pos%5B%5D=rb&draft_pos%5B%5D=wr&draft_pos%5B%5D=te&draft_pos%5B%5D=e&draft_pos%5B%5D=t&draft_pos%5B%5D=g&draft_pos%5B%5D=c&draft_pos%5B%5D=ol&draft_pos%5B%5D=dt&draft_pos%5B%5D=de&draft_pos%5B%5D=dl&draft_pos%5B%5D=ilb&draft_pos%5B%5D=olb&draft_pos%5B%5D=lb&draft_pos%5B%5D=cb&draft_pos%5B%5D=s&draft_pos%5B%5D=db&draft_pos%5B%5D=k&draft_pos%5B%5D=p&c1stat=rec_yds&c1comp=gt&c1val=1000&c5val=1.0&order_by=rec_yds|title=Most seasons of 1,000+ receiving yards by a TE|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Post-season records:''\n* Most receptions by a tight end in [[Super Bowl]] history: 23<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/thehall/status/1102950821283749889?s=21|title=Rob Gronkowski has the most receptions by a TE in Super Bowl history (23). His gloves from #SBLIII are on display at #TheHallpic.twitter.com/w3snkn6o1v|last=Raytheon|first=The Hall presented by|date=March 5, 2019|website=@thehall|language=en|access-date=March 7, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most receiving yards by a tight end in Super Bowl history: 297<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Most career postseason receiving touchdowns by a tight end: 12<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/pgl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=combined&year_min=1950&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=TE&game_type=P&career_game_num_min=1&career_game_num_max=400&game_num_min=0&game_num_max=99&week_num_min=0&week_num_max=99&c1stat=rec_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=3&c5val=1.0&order_by=rec_td|title=Most postseason TDs by a TE|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n* First tight end with 1,000+ career postseason receiving yards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boston.cbslocal.com/2019/01/20/rob-gronkowski-patriots-nfl-postseason-history-1000-receiving-yards/|title=Patriots\u2019 Rob Gronkowski Becomes First Tight End To Hit 1,000 Postseason Receiving Yards|date=January 20, 2019|language=en|access-date=January 27, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most career postseason receiving yards by a tight end: 1,163<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/pgl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=combined&year_min=1950&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=TE&game_type=P&career_game_num_min=1&career_game_num_max=400&game_num_min=0&game_num_max=99&week_num_min=0&week_num_max=99&c1stat=rec_yds&c1comp=gt&c1val=500&c5val=1.0&order_by=rec_yds|title=Most postseason yards by a TE|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n* Youngest player with 3 touchdown receptions in a game, playoffs: 22 years, 275 days (2011 playoffs, vs. [[Denver Broncos]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/pgl_finder.cgi?request=1&match=game&year_min=1950&year_max=2018&season_start=1&season_end=-1&pos%5B%5D=QB&pos%5B%5D=WR&pos%5B%5D=RB&pos%5B%5D=TE&pos%5B%5D=OL&pos%5B%5D=DL&pos%5B%5D=LB&pos%5B%5D=DB&game_type=P&career_game_num_min=1&career_game_num_max=400&game_num_min=0&game_num_max=99&week_num_min=0&week_num_max=99&c1stat=rec_td&c1comp=gt&c1val=3&c5val=1.0&order_by=age&order_by_asc=Y |title=Players with 3 TD in a playoff game, by age |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Records previously set but no longer held:''\n* Most single-season record for receiving yards by a tight end: 1,327 (2011; broken in 2018 by [[George Kittle]])<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===Patriots franchise records===\n* Most career touchdown receptions: 79\n* Most games with multiple touchdowns: 16\n* Most games with 100+ receiving yards by a tight end: 26\n* Highest receiving yards per game average for a tight end (season): 82.9 (2011)\n\n== Football legacy ==\n[[File:Rob Gronkowski.JPG|thumb|Gronkowski in 2017|247x247px]]\nDescribed as an \"NFL supernova,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/patriots/2019/03/24/gronkowski-retires-nothing-less-than-football-folk-hero/llRb5DoBUFAyX4VXqv8vBM/story.html|title=Gronkowski retires nothing less than football folk hero - The Boston Globe|last=Columnist|first=Christopher L. Gasper-|website=BostonGlobe.com|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref> a \"[[sui generis]],\"<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/nfl/gronkowski-retires-nothing-less-than-football-folk-hero/ar-BBVaQJj?ocid=ob-tw-enus-1508523114409|title=Gronkowski retires nothing less than football folk hero|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref> a \u201cgold standard,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/8eee806354004e648a70f43c4c3f42ee|title=Eagles' Ertz so good, but Pats' Gronk is gold standard among tight ends|last=Stapleton|first=Arnie|date=|website=AP News|language=en|access-date=February 19, 2019|quote=\"Gronk is the gold standard.\"}}</ref> a \"generational marvel,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/01/super-bowl-patriots-rob-gronkowski-cost-of-greatness/581650/|title=Rob Gronkowski and the Cost of Greatness|last=O'Connell|first=Robert|date=January 31, 2019|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref> and an \"on-field force of nature,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcsports.com/boston/new-england-patriots/best-belichick-era-number-9-rob-gronkowski|title=Best of the Belichick Era: Number 9 -- Rob Gronkowski|date=July 19, 2015|website=NBC Sports Boston|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref> Gronkowski revolutionized the tight end position and became the envisioned archetype for which the position could and should be.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.southcoasttoday.com/sports/20190201/patriots-rob-gronkowksi-has-set-standard-at-tight-end|title=Patriots' Rob Gronkowksi has set the standard at tight end|last=Mark Daniels|first=Mark|date=|website=southcoasttoday.com|language=en|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2019/02/01/new-england-patriots-dynasty-rob-gronkowski-appreciation|title=Rob Gronkowski is just what this Patriots dynasty needed|website=SI.com|language=en|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegram.com/news/20190201/patriots-tight-end-rob-gronkowski-has-carried-tight-end-position-to-new-heights|title=Patriots: Tight end Rob Gronkowski has carried tight end position to new heights|last=Daniels, @MarkDanielsPJ|first=Mark|website=telegram.com|language=en|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> For [[ESPN]], \"it felt like the tight end position was invented in response to his rare gifts, the singular marriage of power and grace he brought to the game.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/25933118|title=Is this Gronk's last call?|date=February 6, 2019|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nGronkowski was widely praised for his versatility, having both the catching dexterity of a [[wide receiver]] and the blocking skills of an [[offensive lineman]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NFLFilms/status/1092855699728678918|title=Tom Brady sees all! Rob Gronkowski catches all!|last=Inside the|first=NFL|date=February 5, 2019|website=NFL Films on Twitter|language=en|access-date=February 19, 2019|quote=\"His (Tom Brady's) favorite tight end. The all-world tight end.\"}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.profootballfocus.com/news/pro-rob-gronkowski-is-the-nfls-best-offensive-player-patriots|title=What makes Rob Gronkowski the NFL's best offensive player {{!}} PFF News & Analysis {{!}} Pro Football Focus|website=www.profootballfocus.com|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref> Such abilities, both played on elite levels, made him the most complete,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4817187|title=Rob Gronkowski worthy of first-ballot entry to Pro Football Hall of Fame|date=2019-03-24|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref> all-around,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/mar/25/rob-gronkowski-retirement-new-england-patriots-nfl|title=Rob Gronkowski played the goofball but few can doubt his greatness|last=Connolly|first=Oliver|date=2019-03-25|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-03-26|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> and true tight end,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://player.fm/series/ben-and-woods-interviews/brian-baldinger-gronk-defined-what-a-true-tight-end-is|title=Brian Baldinger: \"Gronk Defined What A True Tight End Is\" Ben And Woods - Interviews podcast|last=FM|first=Player|website=player.fm|language=en|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref> unlike other players of his position who were either only a receiver or blocker.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BaldyNFL/status/1100171426974306304|title=Patriots Rob Gronkowski has been the most dominant TE in the NFL for a decade there isn\u2019t a close #2. Will the college game ever produce another complete TE like the GRONK?|last=Baldinger|first=Brian|authorlink=Brian Baldinger|date=February 25, 2019|website=Twitter|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/YahooSportsNFL/status/534194084370333697|title=Man, Gronk, wow. Just eviscerated that guy. The best receiving TE in football can block like a lineman. Unfair.|last=NFL|first=Yahoo Sports|date=November 16, 2014|website=@YahooSportsNFL|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.denverpost.com/2016/01/22/broncos-plan-to-slow-down-patriots-rob-gronkowski-with-physicality-better-tackling/|title=Broncos plan to slow down Patriots\u2019 Rob Gronkowski with physicality, better tackling|last=|first=|date=January 22, 2016|website=The Denver Post|language=en-US|access-date=February 26, 2019|quote=\u201cTotal package, man,\u201d Aqib Talib said in his press conference Thursday, \u201cBest tight end I\u2019ve ever seen play the game, man. It\u2019ll definitely be a tough cover any time he\u2019s split out wide.\u201d}}</ref> Big, strong and agile at 6'6\" and 265-pounds with hands measuring 10 \u00be inches from thumb to pinkie, he has been viewed as a homologue to [[National Basketball Association|NBA]]'s [[LeBron James]] and [[Shaquille O'Neal]] as one of the most physically gifted athletes in American sports history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/boston/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4797082|title=Is Rob Gronkowski the best tight end in the history of the NFL?|date=October 30, 2016|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/nfl/story/new-england-patriots-washington-redskins-jay-gruden-rob-gronkowksi-lebron-james-comparison-110415|title=Jay Gruden compares Gronkowski to LeBron: 'He's going to get his points'|last=Nov 4|first=foxsports|last2=ET|first2=2015 at 5:14p|date=November 4, 2015|website=FOX Sports|language=en-US|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/02/sports/football/gronkowskis-big-hands-are-a-key-to-his-success.html|title=Gronkowski\u2019s Big Hands Are a Key to His Success|last=Shpigel|first=Ben|date=February 1, 2012|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 19, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/videos/good-morning-football/0ap3000000913100/Tony-Gonzalez-Rob-Gronkowski-is-the-Shaquille-O-Neal-of-the-NFL|title=Tony Gonzalez: Rob Gronkowski is the Shaquille O'Neal of the NFL|website=NFL.com|language=en|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> Gronkowski is also known for his high football [[Intelligence quotient|IQ]] and has been acknowledged for his intelligent and versatile route-running.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2754254-nfl1000-ranking-the-top-tight-ends-of-2017-season|title=NFL1000: Ranking the Top Tight Ends of 2017 Season|last=Scouts|first=NFL1000|website=Bleacher Report|language=en|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/mmqb/2016/09/13/rob-gronkowski-patriots-nfls-brainiest-tight-end|title=Rob Gronkowski, Football's Brainiest Tight End|website=SI.com|language=en|access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> He was the highest ranked tight end in the annual [[NFL Top 100|NFL Top 100 Players]], as voted by his peers. Regarded as one of football's finest players, he has set several [[#NFL records|NFL records]] and was selected not only in the [[National Football League 2010s All-Decade Team|NFL 2010s All-Decade Team]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001108338/article/tom-brady-aaron-donald-headline-nfls-2010s-alldecade-team|title=NFL's 2010s All-Decade Team|last=|first=|date=|website=NFL.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> but also in the [[National Football League 100th Anniversary All-Time Team|NFL's 100th Anniversary All-Time Team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/videos/all-time-team/0ap3000001087426/NFL-All-Time-Team-Rob-Gronkowski|title=NFL All-Time Team: Rob Gronkowski|website=NFL.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-15}}</ref> Gronkowski is also widely thought of as the best tight end in the history of the game.<ref name=\"greatest\" />\n\nHis effervescence and irreverence made him not only a fan favorite,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ftw.usatoday.com/2019/03/rob-gronkowski-retires-tom-brady-reacts|title=Tom Brady reacts to Rob Gronkowski's retirement: 'Love u man!!'|date=2019-03-24|website=For The Win|language=en|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref> but also an icon<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcsports.com/boston/patriots/curran-rob-gronkowski-had-nothing-more-give|title=Curran: Gronk had nothing more to give|last=|first=|date=2019-03-24|website=NBC Sports Boston|language=en|access-date=2019-03-25|quote=Gronk proved a 6-6, 260-pound behemoth with muscles on his muscles, a so-so command of the King\u2019s English and the sense of humor of a seventh-grader could become an icon by never being anything but himself.}}</ref> and a folk hero.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/2019/03/25/so-much-gronk/|title=In a Few Short Years, There Was Just So Much Gronk|date=2019-03-25|website=Boston Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> Gronkowski is considered one of the most unique personalities in sports, and has played with \"an inimitable combination of acrobatic athleticism and reckless abandon\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/25/sports/gronk-retires.html|title=Gronk Cruises Away from N.F.L., Leaving a Big Hole|last=Pennington|first=Bill|date=2019-03-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-03-26|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> all the while maintaining his boyish enthusiasm and humor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TheHerd/status/1110232880125485057|title=The evolution of Gronk with the Patriots is a great example for other stars with big personalities|last=Cowherd|first=Herd w/Colin|date=2019-03-25|website=@TheHerd|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/rob-gronkowskis-most-memorable-moments-both-on-and-off-the-field-from-a-wild-nfl-career/|title=Rob Gronkowski's most memorable moments, both on and off the field, from a wild NFL career|website=CBSSports.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\n=== \"Gronk Spike\" ===\n{{quote box\n| align = right\n| width = 28%\n| quote = \"Gronk is a one of a kind person, player and friend. He is one of the most positive people I have ever been around and he loves to have fun. What you see is what you get and whether he is dancing, singing, laughing, or spiking, he is true to himself.\"\n<br>\u2013Teammate [[Tom Brady]], 2015<ref name=\"partying\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/new-england-patriots-rob-gronkowski-partying-deflate-gate-brady-chemistry/|title=Gronk: Partying makes me a better player|work=CBS News|date=July 17, 2015|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}</ref>\n}}Known for his exuberant personality, Gronkowski has been credited in resurrecting the [[Spike (gridiron football)|spike]] as a [[touchdown celebration]] and making it his own.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/02/sports/football/rob-gronkowskis-spiking-resurrects-an-nfl-art.html|title=Rob Gronkowski\u2019s Spiking Resurrects an N.F.L. Art|last=Bishop|first=Greg|date=February 1, 2012|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 24, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/video/clip?id=12258063|title=The Gronk Spike - ESPN Video|date=June 26, 2015|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref> His signature \"Gronk Spike\" has been a product of the less-restrictive scoring celebrations of the NFL compared to high school and college and debuted on September 26, 2010 after scoring his second NFL touchdown.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4811068 |title=The majesty of the Gronk Spike: How it began and why it's so awesome |last=Cimini |first=Rich |date=January 30, 2018 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> It had become a fan phenomenon, with [[MIT Sloan Sports Analytics Conference]] calculating that Gronkowski's arm moves 130'''\u00b0''' with the football leaving his hand at 60 miles per hour delivering 650 pounds of force.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2012/01/20/rob-gronkowskis-td-ritual-becomes-a-fan-phenomenon/ |title=Rob Gronkowski\u2019s TD ritual becomes a fan phenomenon |date=January 20, 2012 |website=Boston Herald |language=en-US |access-date=February 24, 2019 |agency=Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/09000d5d8262a7e5/article/spiketacular-gronks-signature-td-celebration-a-huge-hit |title=Spike-tacular: Gronk's signature TD celebration a huge hit |last=Samano |first=Simon |date=January 20, 2012 |website=NFL.com |language=en |access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2012/01/20/lets-get-physical/ |title=Let\u2019s get Physical |date=January 20, 2012 |website=Boston Herald |language=en-US |access-date=February 24, 2019 |agency=Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/2012/11/05/history-gronkowski-gronk-spike/ |title=A Brief History Of The Gronkowski Spike |last=Siegel |first=Alan |date=November 5, 2012 |website=Boston Magazine |language=en-US |access-date=February 24, 2019}}</ref> He is also known to dance before spiking,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Patriots/status/1038839018597711872 |title=Get it to the GRONK. |date=September 9, 2018 |website=Twitter |language=en |access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Patriots/status/643216258402545664 |title=Score. Dance. Spike. A recap of Gronk's third TD. |date=September 13, 2015 |website=Twitter |language=en |access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nesn.com/2018/09/bill-belichick-enjoyed-rob-gronkowskis-dance-spike-after-week-1-touchdown/|title=Bill Belichick Enjoyed Rob Gronkowski\u2019s Dance/Spike After Week 1 Touchdown|last=Mullen|first=Logan|date=September 10, 2018|website=NESN.com|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref> and in 2012 imitated a [[Queen's Guard]] which he described as \"that [[The Nutcracker|little nutcracker dude]]\" before his touchdown celebration while playing at [[Wembley Stadium]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/gameon/2012/10/28/rob-gronkowski-queens-guard-touchdown-spike-new-england-patriots/1 |title=Patriots' Rob Gronkowski mimics Queen's Guard prior to TD spike |last=Davis |first=Nate |date=October 28, 2012 |website=USA Today |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190226173312/https://www.usatoday.com/story/gameon/2012/10/28/rob-gronkowski-queens-guard-touchdown-spike-new-england-patriots/1/ |archive-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-game-highlights/0ap2000000086245/Gronk-s-royal-celebration|title=New England Patriots tight end Rob Gronkowski's royal celebration|website=NFL.com|language=en|access-date=February 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Outside football==\nIn July 2015, Gronkowski co-wrote a memoir entitled ''It's Good to be Gronk'' with Jason Rosenhaus. It was published by [[Simon & Schuster]]'s and [[Derek Jeter]]'s Jeter Publishing and became a [[New York Times Bestseller|''New York Times'' Bestseller]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/Its-Good-to-Be-Gronk/Rob-Gronk-Gronkowski/9781476755007|title=It's Good to Be Gronk|date=June 13, 2017|isbn=9781476755007|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2015/08/09/sports/|title=Sports and Fitness Books - Best Sellers - August 9, 2015 - The New York Times|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 16, 2019|language=en|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In it, he wrote that he hasn't spent any of his money he has earned through his NFL contracts and strictly lives off the earnings from his endorsement deals and appearance fees. His salary over the first five years was over $10 million,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/13134606/rob-gronkowski-new-england-patriots-says-living-endorsement-money|title=Rob Gronkowski says he hasn't spent any NFL contract money|accessdate=June 23, 2015}}</ref> and is set to earn $54 million overall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/03/25/rob-gronkowski-kept-a-broke-habit-while-making-millions-in-the-nfl.html|title=Rob Gronkowski kept a 'broke habit' while making millions in the NFL|last=Elkins|first=Emmie Martin, Kathleen|date=2019-03-25|website=www.cnbc.com|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Gronkowski entered [[ESPN]]'s \"World Fame 100\" list of most famous athletes in the world; the outlet estimated his endorsement income the past year alone was $8 million.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/feature/story/_/id/26113613/espn-world-fame-100-2019|title=2019 World Fame 100: Who are the biggest names in sports?|website=ESPN.com|access-date=2019-03-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Sponsorships and endorsements ===\nGronkowski has appeared in print, television and online advertisements for brands such as [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/philadelphia/the700level/watch-nikes-gronk-led-star-studded-new-snow-day-commercial-fantastic |title=Watch: Nike's Gronk-led star-studded new 'Snow Day' commercial is fantastic |date=October 29, 2015 |website=NBC Sports Philadelphia |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Dunkin' Donuts]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/news/2012/03/27/dunkin-donuts-gronkowski-sponsorship.html|title=Dunkin' signs 2-year sponsorship with Patriots' Gronkowski|last=van der Pool|first=Lisa|date=March 27, 2012|work=Boston Business Journal|accessdate=December 31, 2013|publisher=American City Business Journals}}</ref> [[Visa Inc.|Visa]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.adforum.com/creative-work/ad/player/34521133/the-big-gronkowski/visa-checkout |title=Visa Checkout - \"The Big Gronkowski\" |website=AdForum |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[T-Mobile]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LoulFeZbMv0 |title=Rob Gronkowski wants T-Mobile on his team {{!}} T-Mobile Commercial |last=T-Mobile |date=February 4, 2014 |website=YouTube |publisher=T-Mobile |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Tide (brand)|Tide]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://adage.com/creativity/work/sport-odor-defense-collection/52571 |title=Rob Gronkowski Plays a Bad Smell in This Tide Ad About Stinky Athletes |last=Jardine |first=Alexandra |date=August 31, 2017 |website=adage.com |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Lyft]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?reload=9&v=z5H79SnDn0I |title=Undercover Lyft with Rob Gronkowski |date=October 25, 2016 |website=YouTube |publisher=Lyft |access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref> [[JetBlue]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/JetBlue/videos/10153397250226843/|title=JetBlue|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-11}}</ref> [[Zynga]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2015/04/07/opendorse-raises-1-75-million-with-plans-to-make-athlete-endorsements-smarter/ |title=Opendorse Raises $1.75 Million With Plans To Make Athlete Endorsements Smarter |last=Heitner |first=Darren |date=April 7, 2015 |website=Forbes |access-date=November 2, 2016}}</ref> [[Cheerios]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/eat-good-do-good-with-honey-nut-cheerios-good-rewards-program-300722526.html |title=Eat Good, Do Good with Honey Nut Cheerios\u2122 Good Rewards Program |website=www.prnewswire.com |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Oberto Sausage Company|Oberto]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kristidosh/2017/10/13/rob-gronkowski-shines-as-brand-ambassador-for-oberto-beef-jerky-in-new-campaign/ |title=Rob Gronkowski Shines As Brand Ambassador For Oberto Beef Jerky In New Campaign |last=Dosh |first=Kristi |date=October 13, 2017 |website=Forbes |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Whey protein|SixStar Pro]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sixstarpro.com/can/post-format-video-can/rob-gronkowski-plan/ |title=Rob Gronkowski \u2013 Plan |date=December 2, 2014 |website=Six Star Pro Nutrition |language=en-CA |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Bodyarmor SuperDrink]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lancemadden/2012/08/14/rob-gronkowski-becomes-endorser-investor-for-bodyarmor-superdrink/|title=Rob Gronkowski Becomes Endorser, Investor for Bodyarmor SuperDrink|last=Madden|first=Lance|date=August 14, 2012|work=Forbes|accessdate=December 31, 2013|publisher=Forbes.com LLC.}}</ref> [[DraftKings]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=DraftKings|website=YouTube|title=Gronk\u2019s How-To Guide To Playing At DraftKings|date=November 10, 2015|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_NvLJJqbGs8|access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> Kids Footlocker,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcsports.com/boston/new-england-patriots/gronk-stars-grown-kids-foot-locker-commercial|title=Gronk stars in \"Grown Up' Kids Foot Locker commercial|date=August 5, 2015|website=NBC Sports Boston|access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> and video games [[Mobile Strike]]<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Mobile Strike|website=YouTube|title=At Home With The Gronkowskis: Episode 1 (Operation Mobile Strike) - Mobile Strategy Game|date=November 11, 2015|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lvNmIZqU52g|access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> and [[Halo 5: Guardians|Halo]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4786990 |title=Rob Gronkowski on Stephen Colbert show: 'I just love Halloween' |last=Reiss |first=Mike |date=October 31, 2015 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> among others.\n\nIn 2012, PLB Sports began manufacturing \"Gronk Flakes\", a frosted cornflakes breakfast cereal named after and endorsed by Gronkowski. Its initial run of 64,800 boxes cost $3.99 each and available at [[Stop & Shop]] supermarkets in New England.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/playbook/dollars/post/_/id/1677 |title=Gronk Flakes hitting New England shelves |last=Rovell |first=Darren |date=September 22, 2012 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> After the success of the cereals, PLB Sports released \"Gronk's Hot Sauce\" in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/boston/nfl/story/_/id/13581358 |title=That's hot: Pats' Gronkowski to debut hot sauce |last=Rovell |first=Darren |date=September 4, 2015 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> The following year Gronkowski and [[Monster Energy]] released a signature \"Gronk\" beverage distributed by [[Coca-Cola]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/14188905/rob-gronkowski-new-england-patriots-signs-monster-energy-drink |title=Pats' Gronkowski signs with Monster energy drink |last=Rovell |first=Darren |date=2015-11-22 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref>\n\nGronkowski has appeared for several advertisements for Tide including commercials for [[Super Bowl LI]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/WNT/video/rob-gronkowski-star-tide-super-bowl-commercial-45260698 |title=Video: Rob Gronkowski to Star in a Tide Super Bowl Commercial |website=ABC News |language=en |access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref> He was the endorser of [[Laundry detergent pod|Tide Pods]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c_vVBuyJZaQ |title=Tide {{!}} Tide PODS\u00ae Talk With Gronk |date=July 17, 2018 |website=YouTube |publisher=Tide |access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref> and consequently partnered with the brand for a [[public service announcement]] discouraging children and teens from [[Consumption of Tide Pods|eating the laundry detergent pods after a viral internet challenge in 2017\u201318]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/ftw/2018/01/12/rob-gronkowski-tells-everyone-not-to-eat-tide-pods-what-the-heck-is-going-on-people/109410444/ |title=Rob Gronkowski tells everyone not to eat Tide Pods |last=Tsuji |first=Alysha |date=January 12, 2018 |work=USA TODAY |access-date=January 13, 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-DrC_PF_3Lg |title=Gronk knows that Tide PODS\u00ae are for DOING LAUNDRY. Nothing else. |date=January 12, 2018 |website=YouTube |publisher=Tide |access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, Gronkowski credited [[Cannabidiol]] (CBD) Oil, the non-[[Psychoactive drug|psychoactive]] component of cannabis plants for making him pain-free for the first time in a decade, and has advocated sports governing bodies to allow players to use it for pain management.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001044528/article/rob-gronkowski-not-returning-in-foreseeable-future |title=Rob Gronkowski not returning in 'foreseeable future' |last=Patra |first=Kevin |date=August 27, 2019 |website=NFL.com |language=en |access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref>\n\n===Film, television and other media===\n\n[[File:Rob Gronkowski in Family Guy.jpg|thumb|left|Gronkowski (right) as an animated version of himself with [[Peter Griffin]] in the ''[[Family Guy]]'' episode \"Gronkowsbees\" in 2017.|275px]]\n\nGronkowski has been featured on the covers of ''[[GQ]],''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gq.com/story/rob-gronkowski-first-gq-cover |title=Rob Gronkowski Just Scored His First GQ Cover! |last=Nast |first=Cond\u00e9 |date=May 12, 2016 |website=GQ |language=en |access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref> ''[[ESPN The Magazine]],''<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/untagged/2014/12/09/rob_gronkowski_opens_up_to_espn_about_fears_after_knee_injur |title=Rob Gronkowski Opens Up to ESPN About Fears After Knee Injury, Relationship with Tom Brady |last=Finn |first=Chad |date=December 9, 2014 |work=Boston.com |access-date=February 17, 2019 |language=en-US}}</ref> ''[[The Body Issue|ESPN The Body Issue]],''<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archive.boston.com/sports/blogs/thebuzz/2012/07/rob_gronkowski_1.html |title=Rob Gronkowski makes cover of ESPN's 'body issue' |last=Silva |first=Steve |work=Boston.com |access-date=February 17, 2019 |language=en}}</ref> ''[[Sports Illustrated]],''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nesn.com/2012/08/rob-gronkowski-lands-on-cover-of-sports-illustrated-nfl-preview-issue-photo/|title=Rob Gronkowski Lands on Cover of Sports Illustrated NFL Preview Issue (Photo)|last=Cole|first=Mike|date=August 29, 2012|website=NESN.com|language=en|access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2015/01/06/new-england-patriots-rob-gronkowski-sports-illustrated-cover |title=SI cover: The Patriots' not-so-secret weapon, Rob Gronkowski |last=Axson |first=Scooby |date=January 6, 2015 |website=SI.com |language=en |access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Muscle & Fitness]]''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.muscleandfitness.com/athletes-celebrities/news/rob-gronkowski-and-everything-nfl-octobers-muscle-fitness |title=Rob Gronkowski and Everything NFL in October's Muscle & Fitness |website=Muscle & Fitness |language=en |access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref> among others.  He was the cover of video sports game ''[[Madden NFL 17]]''  published by [[EA Sports]] in 2016 for [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Xbox 360]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/15520923/new-england-patriots-te-rob-gronkowski-cover-madden-nfl-17 |title=Game on: Gronk gets cover of 'Madden NFL '17' |last=Reiss |first=Mike |date=May 12, 2016 |website=ESPN.com |access-date=May 13, 2016}}</ref> The cover featured the tight end in his signature touchdown celebration called the \"Gronk Spike\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000662373/article/rob-gronkowski-to-be-on-cover-of-madden-nfl-17 |title=Rob Gronkowski to be on cover of 'Madden NFL 17' |last=Rank |first=Adam |date=May 12, 2016 |website=NFL.com |language=en |access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4811068 |title=The majesty of the Gronk Spike: How it began and why it's so awesome |last=Cimini |first=Rich |date=January 30, 2018 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=February 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAn [[Erotic literature|erotica novel]] inspired by Gronkowski called ''A Gronking To Remember,'' written by Lacey Noonan, was published in December 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/pre-nfl-season-gronking-to-remember|title=Why Your Most Important Pre-NFL-Season Read Is This Rob Gronkowski Erotic Fan Fiction|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=GQ|language=en|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> It has been read aloud on broadcast by Gronkowski himself on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'',<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TnXAkEnt5fA |title=Rob Gronkowski Reads Erotic Fan Fiction |date=2015-02-03 |website=YouTube.com |publisher=Jimmy Kimmel Live |access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> as well as [[comedian]] [[Gilbert Gottfried]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/human-interest/2015/01/a-gronking-to-remember-an-interview-with-lacey-noonan-author-of-rob-gronkowski-erotica.html|title=An Interview With Lacey Noonan, Rob Gronkowski Erotica Author|last=Hess|first=Amanda|date=2015-01-06|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> and [[Rapping|rapper]] [[Travis Scott]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/video/clip?id=13666182|title=Travis Scott reads like Gronk on SportsNation - ESPN Video|date=2015-09-16|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref>\n\n{{external media|width=285px|float=right|image1=[https://www.gamecrate.com/sites/default/files/Madden17Covers.jpg Gronkowski's cover] for [[Madden 17]]}}Gronkowski has appeared as fictionalised versions of himself in the 2015 film ''[[Entourage (film)|Entourage]],'' a 2017 episode of ''[[Family Guy]]'' entitled \"[[Gronkowsbees]]\" and has roles in the American crime-drama thriller film ''[[American Violence]]'' (2017) and ''You Can't Have It'' (2017) among others.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/rob-gronkowski-movie-star-2017-1 |title=Rob Gronkowski is starring in two upcoming crime thrillers |last=Knowlton |first=Emmett |date=January 5, 2017 |website=Business Insider |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref> He had been a co-host of ''[[Crashletes]]'' from 2016\u201317 on [[Nickelodeon]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/crashletes-season-two-renewal-nickelodeon-sports-series/ |title=Crashletes: Season Two Renewal for Nickelodeon Sports Series |last=McLennan |first=Cindy  |date=September 1, 2016 |website=TV Series Finale |access-date=October 7, 2016}}</ref> and competed in [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]]'s ''[[Drop the Mic]]'' in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/11/gina-rodriguez-destroyed-rob-gronkowski-in-a-drop-the-mic-rap-battle |title=Gina Rodriguez destroyed Rob Gronkowski in a 'Drop the Mic' rap battle |last=Schwartz |first=Nick |date=November 1, 2017 |website=For The Win |language=en |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> The same year, Gronkowski appeared on ABC's ''[[Shark Tank]]'' when his brother Chris made a deal with [[Mark Cuban]] and [[Alex Rodriguez]] for Chris's company Ice Shaker.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/10/rob-gronkowski-ice-shaker-mark-cuban-a-rod-shark-tank-flip-cup-investment-video |title=The Gronk brothers played flip cup on 'Shark Tank' then walked away with 150k |last=Kerr-Dineen |first=Luke |date=October 16, 2017 |website=USA Today |access-date=June 10, 2018}}</ref> In July 2018, he joined [[Discovery Channel]]'s ''[[Shark Week]]'' where he helped tag endangered [[tiger shark]]s in the [[The Bahamas|Bahamas]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/20/rob-gronkowski-shark-week-diving-bahamas |title=Watch: Patriots' Rob Gronkowski swims with sharks |last=Carroll |first=Catherine |date=July 20, 2018 |website=SI.com |language=en |access-date=February 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.patriots.com/news/gronk-tags-a-tiger-shark-for-shark-week?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Gronk tags a tiger shark for 'Shark Week' |last=Fiske |first=Angelique |date=July 24, 2018 |website=www.patriots.com |language=en-US |access-date=February 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Gronkowski executive produced and hosted [[Verizon Communications|Verizon]]'s [[Go90]] original show ''MVP'' in which \"business owners and entrepreneurs pitch their products or services to a panel of VIP athletes who weigh in with their expert opinion.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/new-england-patriots-star-rob-gronkowski-stars-produces-talent-finding-show-mvp-on-verizon-go90/ |title=Patriots Star Rob Gronkowski Fields Pitches From Entrepreneurs on Verizon go90's 'MVP' |last=Emery |first=Debbie |date=January 25, 2017 |website=TheWrap |language=en-US |access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref> It had 36 episodes in two seasons.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/mvp-rob-gronkowski-new-england-patriots/ |title='MVP' Gets the Super Bowl Treatment as NFL star Rob Gronkowski Returns for Season 2 |last=Emery |first=Debbie |date=September 7, 2017 |website=TheWrap |language=en-US |access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/rob-gronkowski-strips-off-his-shirt-flips-steaks-on-mvp-season-2-video/|title=Rob Gronkowski Strips Off His Shirt, Flips Steaks on 'MVP' Season 2 (Video)|date=October 10, 2017|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter his retirement from professional football, Gronkowski joined [[Fox Sports]] as an analyst for its NFL programming.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/rob-gronkowski-fox-sports-nfl-analystthursday-night-football-pregame-1202755145/|title=Rob Gronkowski Joins Fox Sports As NFL Analyst After Three Super Bowl Wins With Patriots|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|date=2019-10-08|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> making his on-air debut during ''[[Thursday Night Football|Fox NFL Thursday]]'' on October 10, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/10/08/sport/rob-gronkowski-fox-sports-trnd/index.html |title=Rob Gronkowski is back, but this time as an NFL analyst on FOX Sports |last=Kim |first=Allen  |date=October 8, 2019 |website=CNN.com |access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref> Gronkowski co-hosted [[Fox New Year's Eve specials#Fox's New Year's Eve with Steve Harvey|''Fox's New Year's Eve with Steve Harvey'']] in 2019.<ref name=\":11\" /> \n\nIn April 2020, Gronkowski participated as the \"White Tiger\" on the third season of ''[[The Masked Singer (American season 3)|The Masked Singer]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-season-3-episode-10-recap-white-tiger-1203552305/|title=\u2018The Masked Singer\u2019 Reveals the Identity of the White Tiger: Here\u2019s the Star Under the Mask|last=Schneider|first=Michael|last2=Schneider|first2=Michael|date=2020-04-02|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The same month, he and his girlfriend [[Camille Kostek]] starred in the music video of \"I'll Wait\" by [[Kygo]] with vocals by [[Sasha Sloan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edm.com/music-releases/kygo-sasha-slon-ill-wait|title=Kygo and Sasha Sloan Warm Souls with \"I'll Wait\"|last=Stone|first=Katie|website=EDM.com - The Latest Electronic Dance Music News, Reviews & Artists|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\n=== WWE ===\nA lifelong wrestling fan, Gronkowski first made a cameo appearance during the [[Andr\u00e9 the Giant Memorial Battle Royal]] at [[WrestleMania 33]] in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/33/article/rob-gronkowski-mojo-rawley-andre-the-giant-memorial-battle-royal|title=Rob Gronkowski helps Mojo Rawley win the Andre the Giant Memorial Battle Royal|date=April 2, 2017|website=WWE.com|access-date=April 24, 2017}}</ref> In March 2020, he officially signed with WWE with a contract that, per wrestling journalist [[Dave Meltzer]], will only be for a couple of matches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.f4wonline.com/march-16-2020-observer-newsletter-coronavirus-cancellations-rob-gronkowski-more-306441|title=March 16, 2020 Observer Newsletter: Coronavirus cancellations, Rob Gronkowski, more|date=2020-03-12|website=WON/F4W - WWE news, Pro Wrestling News, WWE Results, UFC News, UFC results|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> He hosted [[WrestleMania 36]] which aired on April 4\u20135, 2020,<ref name=\":1022\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wrestlemania/wrestlemania-36/article/wrestlemania-36-two-night-wwe-network-rob-gronkowski-host|title=Unprecedented two-night WrestleMania to be hosted by Rob Gronkowski on WWE Network|website=WWE|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> and won the [[WWE 24/7 Championship]] on the second day of the event, marking his first championship title.<ref name=\"24/722\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/24-7-championship|title=WWE 24/7 Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charity===\n[[File:Rob Gronkowski football camp a 'touchdown' with youth at JBA 150702-F-CX842-139.jpg|thumb|Gronkowski coaching military kids for a two-day football camp at [[Joint Base Andrews]] in [[Maryland]] in 2015.|243x243px]]\nGronkowski set up the Gronk Nation Youth Foundation which is dedicated to \"help kids stay actively involved in school and sports and provide them with the tools needed to help them follow their dreams and live a happy and more successful life\". The foundation provides grants to sports programs with an emphasis on health, community and fitness.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://gronknation.com/pages/foundation |title=Foundation |website=Gronk Nation |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.chase.com/news/081318-kd-rob-gronk |title=Rob Gronkowksi speaks out on having fun\u2014and giving back |last=Miller |first=Shannon Shelton |date=August 14, 2018 |website=Chase.com |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref> He stated, \u201cI created the Gronk Nation Youth Foundation with my family and my friends, because growing up, I had a lot. I had everything as a kid, from playgrounds to sports, and a lot of people to play with, and thus everything I needed to be successful later as an athlete.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-sports/the-softer-smarter-side-of-gronk-107396/ |title=Rob Gronkowski Has a Softer, Smarter Side |last=Frye |first=Andy |date=2017-01-25 |website=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\nAside from his own foundation, Gronkowski has also regularly helped the [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]] and the [[New England Patriots|Patriots]] Foundation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patriots.com/video/gronk-makes-wishes-come-true?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook|title=Gronk makes wishes come true|website=www.patriots.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.patriots.com/news/reflection-rob-gronkowski-s-legacy-goes-beyond-football?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Reflection: Rob Gronkowski's legacy goes beyond football |last=Fiske |first=Angelique |date=March 25, 2019 |website=www.patriots.com |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> In addition, he annually shaves his head for One Mission Buzz Off for kids with cancer.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://boston.cbslocal.com/2018/06/03/rob-gronkowski-buzz-off-for-kids-with-cancer/ |title=Gronkowski Shaves His Head In Support Of Cancer Patients |date=2018-06-03 |website=CBS - Boston |language=en |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> Noted for being generous with his time and resources, Gronkowski has also done several appearances to New England children's hospitals and schools to support local charities.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/new-england-patriots/post/_/id/4787119 |title=The Rob Gronkowski story not often told: Generosity to charitable causes |last=Reiss |first=Mike |date=2015-11-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://theathletic.com/760752/2019/01/11/on-the-field-rob-gronkowski-is-a-superstar-off-it-hes-been-a-superhero/ |title=On the field, Rob Gronkowski is a superstar. Off it? He's... |last=Howe |first=Jeff |date=January 11, 2019 |website=The Athletic |access-date=2019-03-27}}</ref> In 2016, he received the Ron Burton Community Service Award from the New England Patriots for his charitable works and leadership in the local community.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.patriots.com/news/rob-gronkowski-receives-2016-ron-burton-community-service-award-269066?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Rob Gronkowski Receives 2016 Ron Burton Community Service Award |date=August 30, 2016 |website=www.patriots.com |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\nIn March 26, 2019, in his first public appearance since announcing his retirement, he accepted the Merit Award from [[United Service Organizations]] which recognizes \u201cindividuals of outstanding creative talent who are dedicated to serving others through volunteerism, particularly for military.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2019/03/27/rob-gronkowski-accepted-an-award-uso-dinner-hilarity-ensued/ |title=Rob Gronkowski accepted an award at a USO dinner, and hilarity ensued |last=Kilgore |first=Adam |date=March 27, 2019 |website=Washington Post |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref> In April 6, 2019,  he was honored with the Wish Hero Award by the [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]] [[Massachusetts|MA]]/[[Rhode Island|RI]] for his work on granting the 14 wishes of children with life-threatening sicknesses during his professional football career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2019/04/07/rob-gronkowski-makes-his-first-public-appearance-boston-since-retiring/rjwuoYg51Xa7i8ZWksUXFM/story.html |title=Rob Gronkowski makes his first public appearance in Boston since retiring |last=Yang |first=Nicole |date=April 7, 2019 |website=BostonGlobe.com |access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n\nGronkowski and girlfriend [[Camille Kostek]] donated 10,000 masks each to [[Boston Medical Center]] and [[St. Joseph's Regional Medical Center]] during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/2020/03/31/sports/rob-gronkowski-camille-kostek-donate-10000-masks-boston-medical-center/ |title=Rob Gronkowski, Camille Kostek donate 10,000 masks to Boston Medical Center |last=Yang |first=Nicole |date=March 31, 2020 |website=BostonGlobe.com |language=en-US |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Camille_Kostek_in_New_York,_July_2017_2.png|thumb|Gronkowski's longtime partner, [[Camille Kostek]]]]\nSince 2015, Gronkowski has been in a relationship with model [[Camille Kostek]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/new-england-patriots-rob-gronkowski-cheered-on-by-girlfriend-camille-kostek/|title=Patriots' Rob Gronkowski and Girlfriend 'Really Enjoy Being with Each Other,' Source Says|last=Pennington|first=Juliet|date=September 12, 2015|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> They live together in [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newportri.com/news/20190829/meet-budding-middletown-filmmaker-who-has-worked-with-rob-gronkowski-camille-kostek-and-tom-bradys-company |title=Meet the budding Middletown filmmaker who has worked with Rob Gronkowski, Camille Kostek and Tom Brady's company |last=Barrett |first=Scott |date=August 29, 2019 |website=The Newport Daily News |language=en |access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/sports/rob-gronkowski-squats-girlfriend-camille-kostek-sports-illustrated-party/|title=Rob Gronkowski Keeps Himself Fit After Retirement by Squatting Camille Kostek|last=Merrett|first=Robyn|date=May 10, 2019|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref>\n\nGronkowski has stated that [[Clubbing (subculture)|partying]] improved his playing abilities noting, \"You go out and get refreshed, and it just makes you want to go back out on that practice field and keep going hard.\"<ref name=\"partying\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/if-rob-gronkowski-retires-not-enjoying-himself-then-all-doomed-sadness-824842 |title=If Rob Gronkowski isn't enjoying himself, then I guess we're all doomed to sadness |last=Marcin |first=Tim |date=February 28, 2018 |website=Newsweek |language=en |access-date=December 26, 2018}}</ref> During an on-air interview with [[ESPN Deportes]] after an AFC Championship win in 2012 he responded in Spanish answering, \u201c\u00a1Yo soy fiesta!\u201d (literally, \u201cI am party!\u201d) when asked how he will celebrate the victory.<ref name=\":6\" /> The clip went [[Viral video|viral]], and his Gronk Nation, L.L.C. later  [[trademark]]ed the [[catchphrase]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trademark.trademarkia.com/yo-soy-fiesta-85683867.html|title=YO SOY FIESTA Trademark of Gronk Nation, L.L.C. Serial Number: 85683867 :: Trademarkia Trademarks|website=trademark.trademarkia.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Entourage (film)|Entourage]]''\n| As himself\n| Cameo\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017\n|''[[American Violence]]''\n| Brad\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://patriotswire.usatoday.com/2016/12/16/watch-rob-gronkowski-appear-in-trailer-for-american-violence/ |title=Watch Rob Gronkowski appear in trailer for 'American Violence' |date=2016-12-16 |website=Patriots Wire |language=en |access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref>\n|-\n|''You Can't Have It''\n|Officer Wheadon\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mensjournal.com/health-fitness/watch-rob-gronkowski-stars-cop-you-cant-have-it-gronk-est-movie-possible/ |title=Watch: Rob Gronkowski stars as a cop in 'You Can't Have It,' the Gronk-est movie possible |date=2017-02-24 |website=Men's Journal |language=en-US |access-date=2